cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.MM

The paper discusses the design of massive MIMO systems, which are primarily related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The focus on energy efficiency and circuit power consumption suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect to the research. The use of hardware imperfections and system modeling also suggests a potential application in computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the use of multiple antennas and coordinated multipoint techniques may also relate to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
